    "excerpt": "This prayer for the well-being of the Kaiser (Emperor) Nikolai II and his family appears in the siddur <em>Shir Ushvaḥah</em> (1889) . . .",
    "content": "<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nהַנּוֹתֵן תְּשׁוּעָה לַמְּלָכִים<br />\nוּמֶמְשָׁלָה לַנְּסִיכִים<br />\nמַלְכוּתוֹ מַלְכוּת כׇּל עוֹלָמִים<br />\nהַפּוֹצֶה אֶת־דָּוִד עַבְדּוֹ מֵחֶֽרֶב רָעָה<br />\nהַנּוֹתֵן בַּיָּם דָּֽרֶךְ<br />\nוּבְמַֽיִם עַזִּים נְתִיבָה\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThe one who grants salvation to kings,<br />\nand dominion to princes,<br />\nwhose kingdom is an everlasting kingdom;<br />\nwho delivered his servant David from the wicked sword;<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Find 1 Chronicles 21:15.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;<br />\nwho makes a way through the sea,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> i.e., for the Israelites through the Sea of Reeds.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;<br />\nand a path through the mighty waters:<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> again, for the Israelites, through the River Jordan.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nהוּא יְבָרֵךְ וְיִשְׁמוֹר וְיִנְצוֹר וְיַעֲזוֹר<br />\nוִירוֹמֵם וִיגַדֵּל וִינַשֵּׂא לְמַֽעְלָה<br />\nאֶת אֲדוֹנֵֽינוּ הַקֵּיסָר<br />\nניקאלאי אלכסנדראװיטש<br />\nעִם אִשְׁתּוֹ הֲקֵיסָרֶיהָ הַכְבוֹדָהּ<br />\nאלכסנדרא פעאדראװנא<br />\nוְעִם אִמּוֹ הַקֵּיסָרִית הַכְבוֹדָהּ<br />\nמאריא פעאדראװנא<br />\nוְאֶת יוֹרֵשׁ הָעֶצֶר<br />\nגערגי אלכסנדראװיטש<br />\nיָרוּם הוֹדָם׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nmay he bless, guard, protect and help,<br />\nexalt, magnify and highly aggrandize<br />\nour Lord the Emperor<br />\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\">Nikolai (II) Alexandrovich (Romanov)</a><br />\nand with his wife the Empress<br />\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexandra_Feodorovna_(Alix_of_Hesse)\">Alexandra Feodorovna (Alix of Hesse)</a><br />\nand with his honorable Empress mother<br />\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maria_Feodorovna_(Dagmar_of_Denmark)\">Maria Feodorovna (Dagmar of Denmark)</a><br />\nand the heir to the throne<br />\n(Grand Duke) <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_Duke_George_Alexandrovich_of_Russia\">George Alexandrovich</a>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמֶֽלֶךְ מַלְכֵי הַמְּלָכִים<br />\nבְּרַחֲמָיו יְחַיֵּֽהוּ וְיִשְׁמְרֵֽהוּ<br />\nוּמִכׇּל צָרָה וְיָגוֹן וָנֶֽזֶק יַצִּילֵֽהוּ\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMay the supreme King of kings<br />\nin his mercy grant them life and protection,<br />\nand from all trouble, sorrow, and peril deliver them.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n&nbsp;<br />\nוַיְדַבֵּר עַמִּים תַּחַת רַגְלָיו<br />\nוְיַפִּיל שׂוֹנְאָיו לְפָנָיו<br />\nוּבְכָל אֲשֶׁר יִפְנֶה יַצְלִיחַ.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMay [the supreme King of kings]&nbsp;<br />\nsubdue nations beneath his sway,<br />\nand make his enemies fall before him;<br />\nand in every enterprise in which he shall engage may he prosper.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמֶלֶךְ מַלְכֵי הַמְּלָכִים<br />\nבְּרַחֲמָיו יִתֵּן בְּלִבּוֹ<br />\nוּבְלֵב כׇּל יוֹעֲצָיו וְשָׂרָיו<br />\nרַחֲמָנוֹת לַעֲשׂוֹת טוֹבוֹת עִמָּנוּ<br />\nוְעִם כׇּל יִשְׂרָאֵל.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMay the supreme King of kings<br />\nin his mercy inspire his heart<br />\nand the hearts of all her counsellors and princes,<br />\nwith feeling of compassion to deal benevolently with us,<br />\nand with all Yisrael.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבְּיָמָיו וּבְיָמֵינוּ תִּוָּשַׁע יְהוּדָה.<br />\nוְיִשְׂרָאֵל יִשְׁכּוֹן לָבֶטַח<br />\nוּבָא לְצִיּוֹן גּוֹאֵל.<br />\nוְכֵן יְהִי רָצוֹן<br />\nוְנֺאמַר אָמֵן׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nIn his days and in ours may Yehudah be delivered,<br />\nYisrael dwell in safety,<br />\nand a redeemer come to Tsiyon.<br />\nThat this be his gracious will,<br />\nlet us say, Amen.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>This prayer for the well-being of the Kaiser (Emperor) Nikolai II and his family appears in the siddur <em>Shir Ushvaḥah</em> (1889), a copy of which was used by my great-aunt Bessie Grinberg, <em>z&#8221;l</em> (1896-1983), originally of Moinesti in Bacau Province, Moldavia, Romania. (Much gratitude to my cousin, Linda Propas Ross for preserving this siddur.) &#8211;Aharon Varady</p>\n<h3>Source(s)</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_40339\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Siddur-Shir-ushvahah-Prayer-for-the-Royal-Family-of-King-Nikolai-II-1889-scaled-e1635712246673.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-40339\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Siddur-Shir-ushvahah-Prayer-for-the-Royal-Family-of-King-Nikolai-II-1889-scaled-e1635712246673-300x230.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"230\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-40339\" srcset=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Siddur-Shir-ushvahah-Prayer-for-the-Royal-Family-of-King-Nikolai-II-1889-scaled-e1635712246673-300x230.jpg 300w, https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Siddur-Shir-ushvahah-Prayer-for-the-Royal-Family-of-King-Nikolai-II-1889-scaled-e1635712246673-1024x785.jpg 1024w, https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Siddur-Shir-ushvahah-Prayer-for-the-Royal-Family-of-King-Nikolai-II-1889-scaled-e1635712246673.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-40339\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Siddur Shir Ushvaḥah &#8211; Prayer for the Royal Family of King Nikolai II (1889)</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">Notes</span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" style=\"display: none;; display: none;\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\"></span></p></div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container__1\" style=\"\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">Notes</caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Find 1 Chronicles 21:15.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">i.e., for the Israelites through the Sea of Reeds.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >3</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">again, for the Israelites, through the River Jordan.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('+'); } function footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1() { if (jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').is(':hidden')) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); } else { footnote_collapse_reference_container__1(); } } function footnote_moveToReference__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } } function footnote_moveToAnchor__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } }</script>",
